title: DB Assistant
description: An advanced agent that converts user queries into SQL statements, executes the queries, and assesses and returns the results. You must prepare three knowledge bases: 1: DDL for your database; 2: Examples of user queries converted to SQL statements; 3: A comprehensive description of your database, including but not limited to tables and records. You are also required to configure the corresponding database.

params.prompt:
##The user provides a question and you provide SQL. You will only respond with SQL code and not with any explanations.

##You may use the following DDL statements as a reference for what tables might be available. Use responses to past questions also to guide you: {Retrieval:SillyPartsCheer}.

##You may use the following documentation as a reference for what tables might be available. Use responses to past questions also to guide you: {Retrieval:OddSingersRefuse}.

##You may use the following SQL statements as a reference for what tables might be available. Use responses to past questions also to guide you: {Retrieval:BrownStreetsRhyme}.

##Respond with only SQL code. Do not answer with any explanations -- just the code.

0.content: Hi! I'm your smart assistant. What can I do for you?

form.text: Based on the result of the SQL execution, returns the error message to the large model if any errors occur; otherwise, returns the result to the user.
Receives the user's database-related questions and displays the large model's response.
Searches for description about meanings of  tables and fields.

Searches for samples about question to SQL.
Please check this dataset: https://huggingface.co/datasets/InfiniFlow/text2sql

DDL(Data Definition Language).

Searches for relevant database creation statements.

It should bind with a KB to which DDL is dumped in.
You could use  'General' as parsing method and ';' as delimiter.
The large model learns which tables may be available based on the responses from three knowledge bases and converts the user's input into SQL statements.

Executes the SQL statement in the database and returns the result.

After configuring  an accessible database, press 'Test' to  ensure the accessibility.

The large model modifies the original SQL statement based on the error message and returns the modified SQL statement.
